extends NonProbModelChecker
    Super class for explicit-state probabilistic model checkers.

      • checkExpression

        public StateValues checkExpression(Model model,
                                   Expression expr,
                                   java.util.BitSet statesOfInterest)
                            throws PrismException
        Description copied from class: StateModelChecker
        Model check an expression and return a vector result values over all states. Information about states and model constants should be attached to the model. For other required info (labels, reward structures, etc.), use the methods #setModulesFile and #setPropertiesFile to attach the original model/properties files.
        Overrides:
        checkExpression in class NonProbModelChecker
        statesOfInterest - a set of states for which results should be calculated (null = all states). The calculated values for states not of interest are arbitrary and should to be ignored.
        Throws:
        PrismException

                                          ExpressionProb expr,
                                          boolean forAll,
                                          Coalition coalition,
                                          java.util.BitSet statesOfInterest)
                                   throws PrismException
        Model check a P operator expression and return the values for the states of interest.

        expr - The P operator expression
        forAll - Are we checking "for all strategies" (true) or "there exists a strategy" (false)? [irrelevant for numerical (=?) queries]
